def tonum(dfc_row):
    return dfc_row.replace(',', '')

df_countries['Population (2020)'] = np.vectorize(tonum)(df_countries['Population (2020)'])
df_countries['Pop_in_mills'] = np.vectorize(int)(df_countries['Population (2020)']) / 1000000

# strip the IPC class codes
# broad => strip the broader class
def strip_ipc_class(ipc_class, broad):
    classes = ""
    d = 0
    if (broad ==True):
        d = 2
    for i in range(len(ipc_class)):
        if (ipc_class[i] == ':'):
            str = ipc_class[i-3:i-d]
            classes+=','
            classes+=str
    
    return classes[1:]
